					    <!-- IMAGE CREDIT -->
				        													
				<div class="post_content_body_wrapper">
    			<div class="post_header_wrapper">
    									<h1 class="post_title" itemprop="headline">
					Notable Literary Deaths in 2024					</h1>
					<h3>An Incomplete List of the Writers, Editors, and Great Literary Minds We Lost This Year</h3>
				</div>
								<div class="author_info" itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
					<div class="author_name">By&nbsp;<a href="https://lithub.com/author/literary-hub/" itemprop="url"><span itemprop="name">Literary&nbsp;Hub</span></a></div>
					<div class="author_hr"><hr/></div>
					<div class="publish_date">January 2, 2025</div>
				</div>
				<div class="social_links">
										<a href="https://twitter.com/intent/tweet?via=lithub&text=Notable+Literary+Deaths+in+2024&url=https%3A%2F%2Flithub.com%2Fnotable-literary-deaths-in-2024%2F"><span class="social_twitter"></span></a>
					<a href="https://www.facebook.com/sharer.php?u=https%3A%2F%2Flithub.com%2Fnotable-literary-deaths-in-2024%2F&t=Notable+Literary+Deaths+in+2024"><span class="social_facebook"></span></a>
									</div>
									<!-- Begin each blog post -->
					<div class="post_wrapper" style="padding-top:0;">
						<div class="post_inner_wrapper">
					    	<div class="post_wrapper_inner">
								<div class="post_inner_wrapper">
							        
									<span itemprop="articleBody"><p>To the members of the literary community we lost this year, we say a last thank you, and goodbye. You will be missed.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">*</p>
<p>Poet, novelist, and critic <strong>Fred Chappell </strong><a href="https://www.nytimes.com/2024/01/25/books/fred-chappell-dead.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">died on January 4</a> at the age of 87.</p>
<p>Bestselling celebrity biographer <strong>Anne Edwards </strong><a href="https://www.nytimes.com/2024/01/31/books/anne-edwards-dead.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">died on January 20</a> at the age of 96.</p>
<p>Pulitzer Prize-winning Kiowa and American novelist <strong>N. Scott Momaday</strong> <a href="https://www.nytimes.com/2024/01/29/books/n-scott-momaday-dead.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">died on January 24</a> at the age of 89.</p>
<p><strong>Lawrence L. Langer</strong>, scholar of Holocaust literature, <a href="https://www.nytimes.com/2024/02/01/books/lawrence-l-langer-dead.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">died on January 29</a>. He was 94.</p>
<p>Novelist and short story writer <strong>Ellen</strong> <strong>Gilchrist</strong>, author of <em>Victory Over Japan</em>, <a href="https://www.nytimes.com/2024/02/11/books/ellen-gilchrist-dead.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">died on January 30</a> at the age of 88.</p>
<p>Children&#8217;s book illustrator and author <strong>Petra Mathers </strong><a href="https://www.nytimes.com/2024/03/09/books/petra-mathers-dead.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">died on February 6</a> at the age of 78.</p>
<p>Award-winning children&#8217;s book author <strong>Kate Banks </strong><a href="https://www.nytimes.com/2024/03/27/books/kate-banks-dead.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">died on February 24</a> at the age of 64.</p>
<p>Comic book artist <strong>Ramona Fradon </strong><a href="https://www.nytimes.com/2024/02/29/arts/ramona-fradon-dead.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">died on February 24</a> at the age of 97.</p>
<p><strong>Alta</strong>, poet and <a href="https://www.nytimes.com/2024/05/17/books/alta-dead.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">founder of the country&#8217;s first feminist press</a>, Shameless Hussy, died on March 10 at the age of 81.</p>
<p>Novelist, journalist, and screenwriter <strong>Dan Wakefield </strong><a href="https://www.nytimes.com/2024/03/14/books/dan-wakefield-dead.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">died on March 13</a>. He was 91.</p>
<p>Poet and biographer <strong>Neeli Cherkovski</strong> <a href="https://www.nytimes.com/2024/03/29/books/neeli-cherkovski-dead.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">died on March 19</a> at the age of 78.</p>
<p>Prolific science fiction novelist <strong>Vernor Vinge </strong><a href="https://www.nytimes.com/2024/03/28/books/vernor-vinge-dead.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">died on March 20</a> at the age of 79.</p>
<p><strong>Laurent de Brunhoff</strong>, who continued the <em>Babar the Elephant </em>series, which his father created, for almost 70 years, <a href="https://www.nytimes.com/2024/03/22/books/laurent-de-brunhoff-dead.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">died on March 22</a> at the age of 98.</p>
<p><strong>Marjorie Perloff</strong>, scholar of experimental poetry, <a href="https://www.nytimes.com/2024/03/26/books/marjorie-perloff-dead.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">died on March 24</a>. She was 92.</p>
<p>Iraqi-born Israeli writer <strong>Sami Michael </strong><a href="https://www.nytimes.com/2024/04/05/books/sami-michael-idead.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">died on April 1</a> at the age of 97.</p>
<p><strong>Maryse Condé</strong>, the <a href="https://lithub.com/maryse-conde-international-literary-giant-has-died-at-90/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Guadaloupean novelist, playwright, essayist</a>, and “<a class="external" href="https://x.com/amabanckou/status/1775064748645904504?s=20" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Grande Dame of World Letters</a>,” died on April 2 at the age of 90.</p>
<p><a href="https://lithub.com/kaleidoscopic-novelist-john-barth-has-died-at-93/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Kaleidoscopic novelist</a> <strong>John Barth </strong>died on April 2 at the age of 93.</p>
<p><strong>Lynne Reid Banks</strong>, author of <em>The Indian in the Cupboard</em>, <a href="https://www.nytimes.com/2024/04/05/books/lynne-reid-banks-dead.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">died on April 4</a> at the age of 94.</p>
<p>Comics creator and historian <strong>Trina Robbins</strong> <a href="https://www.nytimes.com/2024/04/10/arts/trina-robbins-dead.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">died on April 10</a> at the age of 85.</p>
<p><strong>Faith Ringgold</strong>, multimedia artist and writer and illustrator of children&#8217;s books, <a href="https://www.nytimes.com/2024/04/13/arts/faith-ringgold-dead.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">died on April 13</a>. She was 93.</p>
<p><strong>Helen Vendler</strong>, giant of poetry criticism, <a href="https://www.nytimes.com/2024/04/24/books/helen-vendler-dead.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">died on April 23</a> at the age of 90.</p>
<p>Psychologist, journalist, author, and biographer <strong>Lesley Hazleton </strong><a href="https://www.nytimes.com/2024/05/07/books/lesley-hazleton-dead.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">died on April 29</a> at the age of 78.</p>
<p>Popular historical novelist <strong>C.J. Sansom</strong> <a href="https://www.nytimes.com/2024/05/03/books/cj-sansom-dead.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">died on April 27</a> at the age of 71.</p>
<p><a href="https://lithub.com/remembering-paul-auster/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Novelist, memoirist, and poet</a> <strong>Paul Auster</strong> died on April 30 at the age of 77.</p>
<p>Poet <strong>David Shapiro </strong><a href="https://www.nytimes.com/2024/05/10/books/david-shapiro-dead.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">died on May 4</a>. He was 77.</p>
<p>Canadian author, <a href="https://lithub.com/remembering-alice-munro/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Nobel Prize winner, and master of the short story</a> <strong>Alice Munro</strong> died on May 13. She was 92.</p>
<p>Comic book artist <strong>Don Perlin </strong><a href="https://www.nytimes.com/2024/05/26/arts/don-perlin-dead.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">died on May 14</a> at the age of 94.</p>
<p><strong>Caleb Carr</strong>, author of <a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780812976144" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>The Alienist</em></a>, <a href="https://www.washingtonpost.com/obituaries/2024/05/25/caleb-carr-author-alienist-dies/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">died on May 23</a> at the age of 68.</p>
<p>Influential French publisher <strong>Eric Hazan </strong><a href="https://www.nytimes.com/2024/06/25/books/eric-hazan-dead.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">died on June 6</a>. He was 87.</p>
<p>Novelist and playwright <strong>Shay Youngblood </strong><a href="https://www.nytimes.com/2024/07/01/books/shay-youngblood-dead.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">died on June 11</a> at the age of 64.</p>
<p><strong>Thomas J. McCormack</strong>, l<a href="https://lunch.publishersmarketplace.com/2024/06/obituary-thomas-j-mccormack-92/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">ongtime editorial director of St. Martin&#8217;s Press</a>, died on June 15. He was 92.</p>
<p>Literary critic <strong>Frederick Crews </strong><a href="https://www.nytimes.com/2024/06/24/books/frederick-crews-dead.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">died on June 21</a> at the age of 91.</p>
<p>Towering Albanian writer <strong>Ismail Kadare </strong><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/books/2024/jul/01/ismail-kadare-obituary" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">died on July 1</a> at the age of 88.</p>
<p>Pioneering queer cartoonist and novelist <strong>Mary Wings</strong> <a href="https://www.nytimes.com/2024/08/08/arts/mary-wings-dead.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">died on July 3</a> at the age of 75.</p>
<p>Poet <strong>Stanley Moss </strong><a href="https://www.nytimes.com/2024/07/06/books/stanley-moss-dead.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">died on July 5</a> at the age of 99.</p>
<p>Writer <strong>Gail Lumet Buckley </strong><a href="https://www.nytimes.com/2024/07/26/books/gail-lumet-buckley-dead.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">died on July 18</a> at the age of 86.</p>
<p>Author and journalist <strong>Jill Schary Robinson </strong><a href="https://www.nytimes.com/2024/07/28/books/jill-schary-robinson-dead.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">died on July 19</a> at the age of 88.</p>
<p><strong>Alexander Waugh</strong>, composer, columnist, historian, and part of &#8220;<a href="https://www.nytimes.com/2024/08/03/books/alexander-waugh-dead.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">one of Britain&#8217;s greatest literary dynasties</a>,&#8221; died on July 22 at the age of 60.</p>
<p><strong>Francine Pascal</strong>, author of the <em>Sweet Valley High </em>books, <a href="https://www.nytimes.com/2024/07/29/books/francine-pascal-dead.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">died on July 28</a> at the age of 92.</p>
<p>Irish writer <strong>Edna O&#8217;Brien </strong><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/books/2024/jul/29/edna-obrien-obituary" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">died on July 28</a> at the age of 93.</p>
<p>Bestselling memoirist <strong>Barbara Howar</strong> <a href="https://www.nytimes.com/2024/08/05/books/barbara-howar-dead.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">died on August 2</a>. She was 89.</p>
<p>Music writer and biographer <strong>Charles R. Cross </strong><a href="https://www.nytimes.com/2024/08/20/arts/music/charles-cross-dead.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">died on August 9</a> at the age of 67.</p>
<p>Poet and author <strong>Hettie Jones </strong><a href="https://www.nytimes.com/2024/08/24/books/hettie-jones-dead.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">died on August 13</a>. She was 90.</p>
<p>Award-winning comic book artist <strong>John Cassaday </strong><a href="https://www.nytimes.com/2024/09/18/arts/john-cassaday-dead.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">died on September 9</a> at the age of 52.</p>
<p>Prominent Lebanese novelist <strong>Elias Khoury </strong><a href="https://www.nytimes.com/2024/09/18/books/elias-khoury-dead.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">died on September 15</a>. He was 76.</p>
<p>Journalist<strong> Neil King Jr.</strong>, author of <em>American Ramble</em>, <a href="https://www.nytimes.com/2024/09/27/books/neil-king-jr-dead.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">died on September 17</a> at the age of 65.</p>
<p>Prolific, bestselling thriller writer <strong>Nelson DeMille </strong><a href="https://www.nytimes.com/2024/09/20/books/nelson-demille-dead.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">died on September 17</a>. He was 81.</p>
<p>Novelist <strong>Ella Leffland </strong><a href="https://www.nytimes.com/2024/10/01/books/ella-leffland-dead.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">died on September 18</a> at the age of 92.</p>
<p>Literary theorist <strong>Fredric Jameson </strong><a href="https://www.nytimes.com/2024/09/23/books/fredric-jameson-dead.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">died on September 22</a> at the age of 90.</p>
<p>Writer and fly fisherman <strong>John Gierach </strong><a href="https://www.nytimes.com/2024/10/29/books/john-gierach-dead.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">died on October 3</a> at the age of 77.</p>
<p><a href="https://lithub.com/postmodern-genius-robert-coover-has-died-at-age-92/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Postmodern genius and legendary writers&#8217; writer</a> <strong>Robert Coover</strong> died on October 5. He was 92.</p>
<p>Autobiographical novelist <strong>Lore Segal </strong><a href="https://www.nytimes.com/2024/10/07/books/lore-segal-dead.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">died on October 7</a> at the age of 96.</p>
<p>Bestselling memoirist <strong>Lily Ebert</strong>, who survived the Holocaust, <a href="https://www.nytimes.com/2024/10/09/books/lily-ebert-dead.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">died on October 9</a>. She was 100.</p>
<p>Chilean novelist, screenplay writer, and playwright <strong>Antonio Skármeta </strong><a href="https://www.nytimes.com/2024/10/24/books/antonio-skarmeta-dead.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">died on October 15</a> at the age of 83.</p>
<p><strong>Charles Brandt</strong>, author of the true-crime bestseller <em>I Heard You Paint Houses</em>, <a href="https://www.nytimes.com/2024/10/30/books/charles-brandt-dead.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">died on October 22</a> at the age of 82.</p>
<p><strong>Gary Indiana</strong>, <a href="https://lithub.com/gary-indiana-iconoclast-and-author-has-died/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">the prickly polymath with a dozen lives and careers to his name</a>, died on October 23 at the age of 74.</p>
<p><strong>Dorothy Allison</strong>, <a href="https://lithub.com/dorothy-allison-author-and-force-of-nature-has-died/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">lesbian feminist activist, force of nature,</a> and author of <em><a class="external" href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780452297753" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Bastard Out of Carolina</a>, </em>died on November 6. She was 75.</p>
<p><strong>Bruce Degen</strong>, who illustrated the<em> Magic School Bus</em> books, <a href="https://www.nytimes.com/2024/11/10/obituaries/bruce-degen-dead.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">died on November 7</a>. He was 79.</p>
<p>Hannah Arendt scholar <strong>Jerome Kohn</strong> <a href="https://www.nytimes.com/2024/12/13/books/jerome-kohn-dead.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">died on November 8</a> at the age of 93.</p>
<p>Trinidadian-American writer <strong>Elizabeth Nunez</strong> <a href="https://www.nytimes.com/2024/11/14/books/elizabeth-nunez-dead.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">died on November 8</a> at the age of 80.</p>
<p>Scholar, critic, and poet <strong>Sandra M. Gilbert</strong>, co-author of <em>The Madwoman in the Attic</em>, <a href="https://www.nytimes.com/2024/11/18/books/sandra-gilbert-dead.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">died on November 10</a> at the age of 87.</p>
<p>Popular Japanese poet and translator <strong>Shuntaro Tanikawa</strong> <a href="https://www.nytimes.com/2024/12/06/books/shuntaro-tanikawa-dead.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">died on November 13</a> at the age of 92.</p>
<p>Bestselling novelist <strong>Barbara Taylor Bradford</strong>, author of <em>A Woman of Substance</em>, <a href="https://www.nytimes.com/2024/11/25/books/barbara-taylor-bradford-dead.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">died on November 24</a>. She was 91.</p>
<p>Bestselling Chinese-language romance novelist <strong>Chiung Yao</strong> <a href="https://www.nytimes.com/2024/12/08/books/chiung-yao-dead.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">died on December 4</a> at the age of 86.</p>
<p><a href="https://lithub.com/beloved-poet-nikki-giovanni-has-died-at-81/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Beloved poet and star of the Black Arts Movement</a> <strong>Nikki Giovanni</strong> died on December 9. She was 81.</p>
</span>
									
																		
									<div style="height:15px;"></div>
									
									<div class="post_tag"><i class="fa fa-tags"></i><a href="https://lithub.com/tag/literary-obituaries/" rel="tag">literary obituaries</a><a href="https://lithub.com/tag/notable-literary-deaths/" rel="tag">Notable Literary Deaths</a><a href="https://lithub.com/tag/rip/" rel="tag">RIP</a></div>									
																		
									<br class="clear"/><hr/>
									
